tweet: This relief package will save lives, businesses, and jobs.   So many people are hurting, and I know it's hard to see our way through this. But if we unite as Americans and work together, I promise you, we can come out of this stronger and better than ever.  https://t.co/VXIUnMdD0X

tweet: 86% of Americans, including overwhelming majorities of Republicans, Democrats, and Independents want Congress to act and pass the compromise COVID-19 relief bill.   Congress has been stuck in gridlock for over eight months. It's past time to get this done.

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: Thank you Mayor @MurielBowser. I'm proud of all our Maryland healthcare heroes who are saving lives in our state and across our region. This virus doesn't stop at borders and neither can we. We will get through this together.

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "We not only need to return to our principles, but we must reinvigorate them with commonsense solutions that work for the 21st century challenges we face."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "Ronald Reagan said that 'freedom was never more than one generation from extinction.'  We must heed those words. We cannot take the blessings of liberty for granted.  We must work to secure them for our children and grandchildren."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "America is at a critical crossroads. And unless we begin to change the self-destructive course both parties are on, this mess will simply just repeat itself again in 2024."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "Here's the truth our party need to hear. Divisive rhetoric and toxic politics is alienating large parts of the country.  And no one will listen to our message if they don’t believe we’re listening to them.  We cannot continue failing to expand our tent."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "Too many in both parties have bought into the false narrative that the way you vote is pre-determined by where you were born, where you live, the color of your skin, who you love, or where you worship."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "Reagan stood for bold principles that were universal. For him, a big tent party was not just an electoral imperative. It was also a moral one. He knew that if our party wanted to truly represent America, we could not ignore any part of it."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: These are the same Americans who Ronald Reagan spoke to.  His vision of America isn’t just a relic of some bygone era but an ideal that we can and we should once again aspire to."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: They want a strong America that stands with its allies and for freedom in the world, but that doesn’t take for granted the sacrifices required for it.  They want to stand together with their neighbors and feel proud of their country once again.

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: They want a discourse that tolerates contrary views among a diverse citizenry without turning political adversaries into enemies or doubting their patriotism.  They want a government that protects the vulnerable without dictating how we live our lives.

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "Most Americans want the same thing.  They want humble, tolerant, respectful, and effective leaders, who will work together to find bipartisan, commonsense solutions.  They want us to appreciate that no one of us has all the answers or all the power.

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "Over seventy percent of the rest of us belong to the 'exhausted majority,' who are fed up with politics and who feel forgotten by both political parties and ignored by Washington."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "Americans are not as divided as politics and social media would suggest...The problem is that politicians think the only way to get elected is to feed the extremes to fire up the base. And that the only way to govern is through winner-take-all combat."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "Americans believe in civility and pragmatism. They think straight talk is more valuable than empty rhetoric. These are things that my party is going to have to focus on if we expect to win national elections again."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "We don’t need Washington to dictate. We need Washington to get its act together. We need Washington to make it easier – not harder for us to solve problems. We need Washington to be a partner – not an impediment."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "The solution according to the professional politicians in Washington is to give them more power. More power in Washington won’t fix the divisiveness and dysfunction. It will only impose more dysfunction on more of our lives."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "On the world stage, China threatens not just America’s economy. But also, the values we stand for...Meanwhile, one party in Washington refuses to acknowledge the threat, while the other abandons the very allies we need to confront it."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "The result is a crumbling vision of the American dream. The average citizen is completely fed up with politics as usual. They think that Washington has been fiddling while America burns."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "The cost of education and quality healthcare are out of reach for everyday Americans. One party wants to impose radical solutions that would create more problems than they would solve. And the other party, too often, offers no solutions at all."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "The failure of Washington is made manifest in failing bridges, failing public health, failing schools, and an entire generation of Americans who are falling behind... Roads and bridges crumble while Democrats and Republicans insult each other on social media."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "Struggling families and small businesses have been desperately in need of immediate relief, but instead of working...Congress went on vacation. Contrast that with America’s governors...We understood that in times of crisis, partisan politics must be put aside."

name: Larry Hogan
tweet: "Sadly, Washington insiders seem more concerned with winning arguments than actually advancing bipartisan solutions...They just want to make demands and win arguments. That’s not leadership. That’s just political theater. And most of us are sick and tired of all the drama."
